    "caption": "Fifty names, one mountain shadow.",
    "shortDescription": "The cougar holds the world record for the animal with the most common names — puma, mountain lion, panther, catamount, and over forty others — and it lives in more places than any other wild cat in the Western Hemisphere, from Yukon to Patagonia. It can leap five metres straight up from a standing start. Fun fact: Cougars can't roar — instead they purr like a house cat, and females make a piercing scream during mating season that sounds almost human."
